article.headline: Siena 77, Marist 60
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Alex Franklin scored a season-high 22 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Siena to a 77-60 victory over Marist in Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference action on Tuesday night. Ryan Rossiter added 10 points and seven rebounds in the win. Trailing 58-57 with 11 minutes left in the game, Kenny Hasbrouck completed a traditional three-point play to key a 16-0 Siena run. Siena (5-3, 2-0 MAAC) never looked back, outscoring Marist 20-2 over the game's final 10:49. Ryan Schneider scored 11 points for Marist (3-5, 1-1 MAAC), which also got 10 from Dejuan Goodwin. Despite shooting 46 percent from the field, Marist committed a season-high 26 turnovers, leading to 28 Siena points. Down eight with two minutes left in the first half, Marist rallied thanks to a pair of 3-pointers by Goodwin and trailed 39-37 at halftime.
